// ProjectSelector
// Dropdown for selecting and managing Kodex projects.
// Shows the selected project name, a list of available projects, an Add Project
// button, and a remove-with-confirmation modal.

Project list comes from kodexStore. Errors auto-clear after 3 seconds.
Dropdown closes on outside click or Escape.

FUNCTION ProjectSelector(className, onAddProject) -> JSX               EXPORT
  CALLS: useKodexStore (kodexStore)
  Reads selectedProject, projects, isLoadingProjects, projectsError from store.
  Renders a button showing the selected project display name (falls back to
  basename of path). Clicking the button opens the dropdown if not loading.
  IF open: renders a listbox of project options + optional Add Project button.
  IF showRemoveConfirm: renders a full-screen modal to confirm removal.

---

FUNCTION getBasename(path) -> string
  Returns the last path segment (after the final "/").

---

FUNCTION getDisplayName() -> string
  Returns "Select Project" if nothing selected.
  Looks up the project by path in projects array for its name; falls back to
  getBasename of selectedProject.

---

FUNCTION handleToggleDropdown() -> void
  Toggles isOpen if not loading.

---

FUNCTION handleSelectProject(path) -> void
  Calls setSelectedProject, closes dropdown.

---

FUNCTION handleAddProjectClick() -> void
  Closes dropdown, calls onAddProject callback.

---

FUNCTION handleRemoveClick(e, path) -> void
  Stops propagation, sets showRemoveConfirm to the project path.

---

FUNCTION handleRemoveProjectConfirm(path) -> void
  Calls removeProject(path). IF successful, clears showRemoveConfirm and closes
  dropdown.

---

FUNCTION handleRemoveProjectCancel() -> void
  Clears showRemoveConfirm without removing the project.
